subway_df['transit_timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(subway_df['transit_timestamp'], format="%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

if 'weekend' not in subway_df.columns:
    subway_df['weekend'] = subway_df['transit_timestamp'].dt.dayofweek.apply(lambda x: 1 if x in [5, 6] else 0)
weekday_df = subway_df[subway_df['weekend'] == 0]

ridership_by_borough = (
    weekday_df.groupby('borough')['ridership']
    .agg(['sum', 'mean'])  # Calculate total (sum) and average (mean) ridership
    .reset_index()
    .rename(columns={'sum': 'total_ridership', 'mean': 'average_ridership'})
)

In [11]:
borough_data = {
    'Manhattan': {'population': 1645867},
    'Brooklyn': {'population': 2679620},
    'Queens': {'population': 2360826},
    'Staten Island': {'population': 492925},
    'Bronx': {'population': 1331144}
}

borough_stats = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(borough_data, orient='index').reset_index()
borough_stats.rename(columns={'index': 'borough'}, inplace=True)

# Group by borough to calculate total ridership
ridership_by_borough = (
    weekday_df.groupby('borough')['ridership']
    .sum()
    .reset_index()
    .rename(columns={'ridership': 'total_ridership'})
)

borough_stats = borough_stats.merge(ridership_by_borough, on='borough', how='left')

borough_stats['ridership_per_capita'] = borough_stats['total_ridership'] / borough_stats['population']

print(borough_stats)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(borough_stats['borough'], borough_stats['ridership_per_capita'], color='orange')
plt.title('Ridership per Capita by Borough (Weekdays)', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Borough', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Ridership per Capita', fontsize=14)
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

weekday_df.loc[:, 'transit_timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(weekday_df['transit_timestamp'], format="%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

weekday_df.loc[:, 'date'] = weekday_df['transit_timestamp'].dt.date
weekday_df.loc[:, 'hour'] = weekday_df['transit_timestamp'].dt.hour

# 7 days data
latest_7_days = weekday_df['date'].sort_values().unique()[-7:]  # Get the last 7 unique dates
filtered_df = weekday_df[weekday_df['date'].isin(latest_7_days)]

hourly_ridership_by_day = (
    filtered_df.groupby(['date', 'hour'])['ridership']
    .sum()
    .reset_index()
)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
for date in latest_7_days:
    day_data = hourly_ridership_by_day[hourly_ridership_by_day['date'] == date]
    plt.plot(day_data['hour'], day_data['ridership'], marker='o', label=str(date))

plt.title('Hourly Ridership for the Latest 7 Days', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Hour of the Day', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Total Ridership', fontsize=14)
plt.xticks(range(0, 24))
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.legend(title='Date', loc='upper left', fontsize=10)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
In [16]:
from datetime import timedelta
weekday_df.loc[:, 'transit_timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(weekday_df['transit_timestamp'], format="%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

latest_date = weekday_df['transit_timestamp'].max().date()

# one month data
one_month_ago = latest_date - timedelta(days=30)
filtered_df = weekday_df[weekday_df['transit_timestamp'].dt.date >= one_month_ago]

filtered_df.loc[:,'date'] = filtered_df['transit_timestamp'].dt.date
filtered_df.loc[:,'hour'] = filtered_df['transit_timestamp'].dt.hour

hourly_ridership_by_day = (
    filtered_df.groupby(['date', 'hour'])['ridership']
    .sum()
    .reset_index()
)

unique_dates = sorted(filtered_df['date'].unique())

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
for date in unique_dates:
    day_data = hourly_ridership_by_day[hourly_ridership_by_day['date'] == date]
    plt.plot(day_data['hour'], day_data['ridership'], marker='o', label=str(date))

plt.title('Hourly Ridership for the Past Month', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Hour of the Day', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Total Ridership', fontsize=14)
plt.xticks(range(0, 24))
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.legend(title='Date', loc='upper left', fontsize=10, ncol=2)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
